hm2AgentMulticastIGMPAdminMode.name: hm2AgentMulticastIGMPAdminMode
hm2AgentMulticastIGMPAdminMode.description: This enables or disables IGMP on the system.

hm2AgentMulticastIGMPProxyOperStatus.name: hm2AgentMulticastIGMPProxyOperStatus
hm2AgentMulticastIGMPProxyOperStatus.description: The operating status of IGMP proxy on this device.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMAdminMode.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMAdminMode
hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMAdminMode.description: This enables or disables PIM Sparse Mode on the system.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingTable.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingTable
hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing BSR-specific information about PIM group mappings learned via C-RP advertisements or created locally using configurations.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingEntry.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingEntry
hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingTable.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpAdd.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpAddrType
hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpAdd.description: The Inet address type of the IP multicast group prefix.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpAdd.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpAddr
hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpAdd.description: The IP multicast group address that, when combined with hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpPrefixLen, gives the group prefix for this mapping. The InetAddressType is given by the hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpAddrType object.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingRPAddr.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingRPAddrType
hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingRPAddr.description: The Inet address type of the RP address.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingRPAddr.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingRPAddr
hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingRPAddr.description: The IP address of the RP to be used for the given group. The InetAddressType is given by the hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingRPAddrType object.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingOrigin.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingOrigin
hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingOrigin.description: The mechanism by which the RP for the group was learned.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpPre.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpPrefixLen
hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpPre.description: The multicast group prefix length that, when combined with hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpAddr, gives the group prefix for this mapping. If hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpAddrType is 'ipv4' or 'ipv4z', this object must be in the range 4..32. If hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingGrpAddrType is 'ipv6' or 'ipv6z', this object must be in the range 8..128.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingExpiry.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingExpiryTime
hm2AgentMulticastPIMSMGroupMappingExpiry.description: The minimum time remaining before this entry will be aged out. The value zero indicates that this entry will never be aged out.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMDMAdminMode.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMDMAdminMode
hm2AgentMulticastPIMDMAdminMode.description: This enables or disables PIM Dense Mode on the system.

hm2AgentMulticastPIMDMPruneAssertHoldtim.name: hm2AgentMulticastPIMDMPruneAssertHoldtime
hm2AgentMulticastPIMDMPruneAssertHoldtim.description: The value inserted into the Holdtime field of a PIM-DM Prune message sent on any interface.

hm2AgentMulticastRoutingAdminMode.name: hm2AgentMulticastRoutingAdminMode
hm2AgentMulticastRoutingAdminMode.description: This enables or disables Multicast Routing Mode on the system.

hm2AgentMulticastSoftwareDSCP.name: hm2AgentMulticastSoftwareDSCP
hm2AgentMulticastSoftwareDSCP.description: Configures the DSCP value that is written into multicast packets that are routed in software. If set to 64, the DSCP value of incoming packets is not changed.

hm2AgentMulticastDVMRPAdminMode.name: hm2AgentMulticastDVMRPAdminMode
hm2AgentMulticastDVMRPAdminMode.description: This enables or disables DVMRP on the system.

hm2AgentSnmpDVMRPTrapFlag.name: hm2AgentSnmpDVMRPTrapFlag
hm2AgentSnmpDVMRPTrapFlag.description: This enables or disables DVMRP Traps on the system.

hm2AgentSnmpPIMTrapFlag.name: hm2AgentSnmpPIMTrapFlag
hm2AgentSnmpPIMTrapFlag.description: This enables or disables PIM Traps on the system.

hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteTable.name: hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteTable
hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteTable.description: The table listing the Static Multicast Route Entries.

hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteSrcAddressType.name: hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteSrcAddressType
hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteSrcAddressType.description: The address type of this Multicast data source.

hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteSrcIpAddr.name: hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteSrcIpAddr
hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteSrcIpAddr.description: The address of the Multicast data source.

hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteSrcNetMask.name: hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteSrcNetMask
hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteSrcNetMask.description: The network mask for the IP address of the Multicast data source.

hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteRpfIpAddr.name: hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteRpfIpAddr
hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteRpfIpAddr.description: The RPF Address. This object has been deprecated, because it has no address type. It is replaced by hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteExtRpfIpAddr.

hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteIfIndex.name: hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteIfIndex
hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteIfIndex.description: The interface index is valid only for IPv6 and only if RPF address is link-local.

hm2AgentIpStaticMRoutePreference.name: hm2AgentIpStaticMRoutePreference
hm2AgentIpStaticMRoutePreference.description: The preference of this route entry.

hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteStatus.name: hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteStatus
hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteStatus.description: The status of this row. The status object cannot be set to active(1) before a valid value has been written to hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteExtRpfIpAddr. All writeable objects in this entry can be modified when the status of this entry is active(1).

hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteExtRpfIpAddrType.name: hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteExtRpfIpAddrType
hm2AgentIpStaticMRouteExtRpfIpAddrType.description: The address type of the RPF Address.

pimBsrCandidateBSRAdvInterval.name: pimBsrCandidateBSRAdvInterval
pimBsrCandidateBSRAdvInterval.description: A Candidate BSR generates Candidate-BSR-Advertisements periodically. This object represents the time interval in seconds between two consecutive advertisements.

hm2AgentMulticastMgmdExtTable.name: hm2AgentMulticastMgmdExtTable
hm2AgentMulticastMgmdExtTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the upstream interface of the router. This is also known as proxy interface.

hm2AgentMulticastMgmdExtEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing the upstream interface of the router.

hm2AgentMulticastMgmdUnsolicitRprtInterv.description: Specify how often the system should send unsolicited reports to routers on the upstream interface.

hm2AgentMulticastMgmdNumberOfGroups.name: hm2AgentMulticastMgmdNumberOfGroups
hm2AgentMulticastMgmdNumberOfGroups.description: Number of groups corresponding to the proxy interface.

hm2AgentMulticastMgmdHostCacheExtTable.name: hm2AgentMulticastMgmdHostCacheExtTable

hm2AgentMulticastMgmdHostCacheExtEntry.name: hm2AgentMulticastMgmdHostCacheExtEntry
hm2AgentMulticastMgmdHostCacheExtEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a group of upstream interface of the router.
